so that people won’t have as much to drink.To come up with their results, 41 male students drank tea from cups marked with either red or blue labels. The students drank 44 percent less from the red cups.To test eating habits, 109 people were served ten pretzels each, either on red, blue, or white plates. Those with red plates ate less pretzels than the rest.Click here to read more on this story from The Daily Mail.Share This ArticleNewsletter SignupSign up for free e-mail news alerts from FoxNews.com and FoxBusiness.com.Newsletter SignupView ArticlePlease enable JavaScript to view the comments powered by Disqus.You must login to comment.View ArticleAdvertisementTop Health CentersBack PainBeauty & SkinCancerCholesterolCold and FluDepressionDigestive HealthHeart DiseaseNutritionPain ManagementPregnancySexual HealthView All Health Centers »FOLLOW FOX NEWS HEALTHYoung GunsBetting on Financial News Startup BenzingaMarketing Startup That Doesn't Feel ManufacturedYoung Guns Reloaded: Wedding Bells, Babies and BusinessYoung Guns: Organic Baby Food SoarsMore ›Latest Health VideosTrending In Health1Prevent cancer with ‘poor man’s pepper’2Louisiana toddler dies after 2-year battle with rare skin disease3Transplant nurse donates kidney to patient4Serious injuries triple for headphone-wearing pedestrians5Woman loses arm, shoulder after injecting bath saltsSee all trendsAdvertisementMeaning Of FingersHealthy Eating And EducationRunning PlaylistDon't Bring Her To The GymCollege Football Programs7 steps to instant calmHow to fight stubborn heartburnFibromyalgia: a tricky diagnosis12 secrets for better orgasmsDiet tips for Crohn's diseaseGerman ZEW Econ. Sentiment Gauge Rises In JanuaryEuro-zone December Annual Inflation Falls To 2.7%U.K. CPI Inflation Drops To 4.2% In DecemberChina Fourth-quarter GDP Up 8.9%, Beats EstimatesFrance Sells 8.6 Bln Euros Of Bills, Yields Slip6 Diet Trends to SkipWhat Do Common Symptoms Tell You?A Guide to Common Dental Problems6 Easy Resistance Band Ex